    <div class="govuk-grid-row">
        <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
            <div class="pins-step-by-step-section-main">
                <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="attending-the-preliminary-hearing">Attending the preliminary hearing</h2>
                <p class="govuk-body">To get involved at this stage, you must be registered to have your say, and have an interested party reference.</p>
                <p class="govuk-body">After the registration period has closed, you will be invited to a Preliminary Meeting. This is to talk about how the application will be examined.
                <p class="govuk-body">You cannot give your views about the proposed development at this stage.
                <p class="govuk-body">You can talk about:
                <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                                <li>any issues with travel or working patterns that affect your ability to attend hearings</li>
                                <li>any other local events happening at the same time</li>
                                <li>if there are any suitable local places to hold the hearings</li>
                                <li>if there are any groups of people who need a different approach to be able to take part in the process</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="govuk-body">
                                <a class="govuk-link" href="#">Advice Note 8.3: Influencing how an application is Examined: the Preliminary Meeting.pdf</a>
                            </p>
                            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="what-happens-next">What happens next</h2>
                            <p class="govuk-body">A week after the preliminary meeting, the Planning Inspectorate will publish the details of the meeting on the website. The detailed examination of the project starts the next day.</p>
                            <p class="govuk-body">Everyone who registered to have their say will be contacted to let them know when they can submit further comments and what to do next.</p>
                            <div class="pins-step-by-step-navigation pins-step-by-step-navigation-next">
                                <a class="govuk-link" href="/interested-party-guide/have-your-say-examination">
